         y=Xploder(y)
    }

A double forward slash is how you mark the start of a comment, so this:

    for (x=0; x&lt;1; x++) {
      while ( (j &lt; y//2) ) 
         y=Xploder(y)
    }

is parsed as this:

    for (x=0; x&lt;1; x++) {
      while ( (j &lt; y y=Xploder(y)
    }


... which explains the error message.

